\[\overrightarrow{AB} \times \overrightarrow{AC} = \begin{pmatrix} 1 - (-t) \\ 3 - 1 \\ 2 - 1 \end{pmatrix} \times \begin{pmatrix} t - (-1) \\ 1 - 1 \\ 1 - 2 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} t + 1 \\ 2 \\ -t - 1 \end{pmatrix} \times \begin{pmatrix} t + 2 \\ 0 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 2t + 2 \\ t^2 + 3t + 2 \\ -2t - 3 \end{pmatrix}.\]Thus, the area of $\triangle ABC$ is
\[\frac{1}{2} \cdot AB \cdot h = \frac{1}{2} \cdot \|\overrightarrow{AB} \times \overrightarrow{AC}\| \cdot \frac{\|\overrightarrow{AB}\|}{\|\overrightarrow{AB}\|} = \frac{\|\overrightarrow{AB} \times \overrightarrow{AC}\|}{2 \|\overrightarrow{AB}\|} = \frac{\sqrt{(2t + 2)^2 + (t^2 + 3t + 2)^2 + (-2t - 3)^2}}{2 \sqrt{2^2 + 1^2 + 1^2}}.\]We want to minimize this, so we minimize the square of the expression under the square root sign:
\begin{align*}
&(2t + 2)^2 + (t^2 + 3t + 2)^2 + (-2t - 3)^2 \\
&\qquad = t^4 + 10t^3 + 33t^2 + 40t + 18 \\
&\qquad = (t^4 + 6t^3 + 9t^2) + (4t^3 + 24t^2 + 36t) + (20t^2 + 4t + 18) - 9t^2 \\
&\qquad = (t^2 + 3t)^2 + 4t(t^2 + 6t + 9) + 20(t^2 + 2t + 1) - 9t^2 \\
&\qquad = (t^2 + 3t)^2 + 4t(t + 3)^2 + 20(t + 1)^2 - 9t^2 \\
&\qquad = t^4 + 22t^3 + 105t^2 + 124t + 44.
\end{align*}This factors as $(t + 2)(t + 1)^2 (t^2 + 4t + 11),$ so the minimum value is $\boxed{\frac{2 \sqrt{29}}{3}}.$

Solution:
We have that
\begin{align*}
y &= 4^t - 5 \cdot 2^t - 1 \\
&= (2^t)^2 - 5 \cdot 2^t - 1 \\
&= (2^t)^2 - 2 \cdot 2^t - 3 \cdot 2^t - 1 \\
&= (2^t - 3)(2^t + 1) - 2.
\end{align*}Thus, the plotted points lie on a curve of the form $(x,y) = (t, (2^t - 3)(2^t + 1) - 2).$

