This is a $\boxed{\text{(C) Parabola}}.$

We claim that all plotted points lie on a hyperbola.

Note that
\begin{align*}
x + 3 &= 2^t, \\
y + 1 &= 4^t - 5 \cdot 2^t = (2^t)^2 - 5 \cdot 2^t = (2^t - 5)(2^t).
\end{align*}Then
\[\frac{x + 3}{2^t} - 1 = 2^t - 5.\]Let $u = 2^t.$  Then
\[\frac{x + 3}{u} - 1 = u - 5.\]Hence,
\[\frac{x + 3}{u} - u + 4 = 0.\]This is the equation of a hyperbola.

